result.execSummary:
The defendant Walter J. Thomas was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Walter J. Thomas appeared by video, in custody of Jackson County Jail, Attorney Carly June Sebion appeared by video for Walter J. Thomas, Attorney Crystal Leigh Jensen appeared in court for State of Wisconsin. Case 21CT74 is being heard specially by Judge Becker for judicial efficiency.  Case 21CT74 is dismissed but read in for sentencing.
Court finds he understood and wishes to proceed today remotely. Defendant plead no contest to count 3. Court reviewed the elements and potential penalties of the charge the defendant plead to.  He understood.   Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant. Felony warnings given.  He understood. Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of Count 3 -Bail Jumping-Felony contrary to 946.49(1)(b). Defendant did not exercise his right to allocution.
Atty Sebion will update clerk of his current address.

Count 1, 2 and 4 are DRI along with the charges in 21CT74.

Joint recommendation of 75 day jail sentence with 50 day credit plus costs and DNA on file.  Payment plan requested.  

Court adopts the joint recommendation. Orders straight sentence of 75 days jail with 50 days jail credit. Ordered to pay court costs.  Payment plan of $25/month starting May 1, 2022. DNA on file.
